The Niger State governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani Bello, on Monday, declared a curfew in the state from 8am to 8pm till further notice. The curfew will begin from Wednesday. Governor Bello made the declaration while addressing journalists at the Government House in Minna. The state government also prohibited all public gatherings of more than 20 people. Street hawking and begging are also banned in the state. 